Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:45.22,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,As ancient adage dictates: \NThe world under heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.22,0:03:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Long divided, must unite.\NLong united, must divide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:54.02,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: 771 BC – 476 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:54.02,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,In the times of Spring and Autumn,\Nfive hegemons strove for supremacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.22,0:03:57.73,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: 475 BC – 221 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.22,0:03:57.73,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,In the times of Warring States,\Nseven kingdoms clashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.35,0:04:04.04,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,After five centuries of strife, they were quelled and united under Qín.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:09.67,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,After the Qín fell,\Ntwo rival nations arose: Chǔ and Hàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.98,0:04:13.97,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,Thus all were once again\Nunited under the Hàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:22.31,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,In the 2nd year of Zhānghe\Nof the Eastern Hàn dynasty,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:22.31,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: 88 AD
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.62,0:04:26.22,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,the ten-year-old Emperor Hé of Hàn\Nascended the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.71,0:04:31.02,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,With the help of eunuchs, he was able\Nto depose Empress Dowager Dòu
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.02,0:04:34.75,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,along with her elder brother,\NGeneralissimo Dòu Xiàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.53,0:04:38.08,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,Eunuchs became a part of government function,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.20,0:04:43.71,Default Song version,,0,0,0,,thus their domination marked the\Nbeginning of the end for the Hàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.37,0:04:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.13,0:04:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live His Majesty!
